SOCIETE des Bains de Mer, the company that controls most of the grand hotels
and casinos in Monaco, suffered a slight fall in net profits during the
first half of the year.
The company, which owns the Hotel de Paris in Monte Carlo as well as the
main casino, saw net profits slip by 4.6 per cent to FFr107.6m (Dollars
20.24m) in the six months to September 30 1992 from FFr112.6m in the same
period last year.
By contrast, interim turnover rose by 5.6 per cent to FFr1.56bn.
Rhone-Poulenc Rorer, the US-based pharmaceuticals subsidiary of
Rhone-Poulenc, France's flagship chemicals group, made a profit of Dollars
258m from the sale and leaseback of its headquarters to an unidentified US
investment group. The proceeds will be used to reduce the company's debt.
